(193, 1, '2021-11-07 22:49:05', '2021-11-07 22:49:33', '2021-11-07', '22:32:00', NULL, 'EST', 18000, 'How the day is going so far', 'I woke up late and went to the Young Israel of Lawrence-Cedarhurst for the 9AM minyan (new time). I enjoyed the chocolate chip muffin and coffee there as well. ×©×—×¨×™×ª was taking a little too long because of a slow ×—×–×Ÿ so I left before ×©×—×¨×™×ª was over. I couldnâ€™t get any college homework done in the morning and was groaning about it. My training friend from Atlantic Beach came to my house and spoke to my parents about me. I went to my therapist meanwhile and told him that I want some percentage of the Hogwarts experience and make friends the way Harry Potter did. He told me that itâ€™s not possible and that no one makes friends that fast. I came back home and my training friend was still there but I had to take a haircut first (there was a barber that came to my house). I then joined the conversation and my training friend was trying to tell me that friends donâ€™t have to be my age. I told him about how much I would be missing out on by not having a friend in my own age group and told him about that, for example, we might be eating pizza together and then see a bunch of high school boys enjoying themselves which I would be jealous of. He told me â€œno examplesâ€ and that it might look like those high school boys are having their best lives, but in reality, they might be semi-suicide. Iâ€™ll try it out but I would really love to be with friends in my age group that do things together like Harry Potter did. I see that itâ€™s not possible now. Now I have the urge to create another website showing an application form to the autism school that would be modeled after Hogwarts. The problem is the overloading college homework. I canâ€™t even get on top of my personal website now.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1),
(194, 1, '2021-11-08 13:05:15', '2021-11-08 13:05:15', '2021-11-08', '12:59:00', NULL, 'EST', 18000, 'How my morning is going so far', 'I decided that I want to break free of my parents strict rules for dress codes and wear a NASA t-shirt. My parents restrict what I can wear to just white button down shirts or polo shirts with collars. Iâ€™m actually going to go even further than that. I asked a co-worker to bring in a modern yarmulke and he told me that he will. Iâ€™m looking forward to how people will react in Landers College which is the most yeshivish college in the world.', 'me-with-a-nasa-tshirt.jpg', 1, 'Me with a NASA tshirt', NULL, 1),
